## Deactivate a Specific Employee

```shell
curl -X PUT "<%= config[:base_url] %>/employees/<ID>" \\
     -H 'x-api-key: <%= config[:api_key] %>' \\
     -H 'tio-auth-token: <%= config[:api_token] %>' \\
     -d $'{
        "data": {
          "id": "4064",
          "type": "employees",
          "attributes": {
            "is-active": false
          }
        }
      }'
```

This endpoint deactivates a specific employee.

### HTTP Request

`PATCH <%= config[:base_url]%>/employees/<ID>`

### URL Parameters

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------
ID | The ID of the employee to deactivate

### BODY Parameters

Parameter | Type    | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
is-active | boolean | To deactivate an employee, `is-active` must be false